node.title: Massive fire breaks out at New Jersey chemical factory
node.description: It's not yet clear what caused the fire or if anyone was injured.
node.content: ["A eight-alarm fire broke out Friday night at a chemical factory in Passaic, New Jersey, officials said. The three-story building caught fire at approximately 8:30 p.m., CBS New York reported.\u00a0", "Video taken by a CBS New York reporter on the scene showed smoke billowing from a large blaze, which the Wood-Ridge Fire Department said was an eight-alarm fire. It's not yet clear what caused the fire or if anyone was injured.\u00a0", "Large fire at a chemical plant in Passaic New Jersey. The mayor is asking nearby residence to keep their windows closed.  @CBSNewYork pic.twitter.com/mLVrSjdwql", "Passaic Mayor Hector Carlos Lora warned nearby residents to keep their windows closed and avoid the area on Facebook Live, calling it an \"extremely serious\" fire. The New York City emergency management system also warned residents that they might see or smell smoke from the fire. \u00a0", "This is a developing story. It will be updated.\u00a0", "Victoria Albert is a News Editor at CBS News. Reach her at victoria.albert@viacomcbs.com"]
